On 3/1/06, jason r tibbetts &lt;tibbettj@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; On that note, what conventions does everyone here use to name their test
&gt; methods? For this example, mine would look like:
&gt;
&gt; test_push_emptyStack()
&gt; test_push_stackWith1Element()
&gt; test_push_fullStack()
&gt; test_push_nullElement()
&gt;
&gt; in other words,
&gt;    &quot;test&quot; + /primary/ method under test + scenario description
&gt;
&gt;
I try to have the method name give some indication of what /should/ happen.

testStackShouldContainOneElementAfterPush
testStackShouldContainTwoElementsAfterTwoPushes

The discipline of coming up with a sentence with /should/ in it helps me to
focus on what the test is really testing. I was surprised by how effective
this turned out to be.

Kevin


